lomse README file
Version: v0.0
Last update: 2012-Feb-04
--------------------------

LenMus open music score edition library (Lomse library) for C++ is a free open 
source library to add capabilities to any program for editing, rendering and 
playing back music scores. It is witten in C++ and it is platform independent, 
and developed using TDD (Test Driven Development).

Lomse is based on the experience gained developping the LenMus project 
(www.lenmus.org) and it is, currently a work in progress.

Lomse is free software distributed under the terms of the BSD 2-Clause License. 


website:    http://lomse.sourceforge.net/
email:      cecilios@users.sourceforge.net

